If you truly know me, you know my tension releaser, my other passion, my side hustle... is baking!!
Reunited with my dear friend to make holiday goodies! It's been awhile since we did our holiday candy making together @christinemmcgrath!! 
Good times finished off with that deliciously soothing winter hot tub session. ❄🥰

We made Buckeyes (Chestnuts), Chocolate Covered Cherries, and Vanilla & Chocolate Oreo Balls. Still have to finish Peppermint Patties & Chocolate Covered Coconut Balls... we had enough rolling & dipping for one day! 😂

Some of you may know that my first career was in dance. It was my life for almost 25 years... then I stopped for 28 years to focus on my nail career. Only recently have I reconnected...but this time with salsa dancing. 💃

This weekend I will be performing with our student team from @lilatinmovement and I'm filled with nervous excitement! It's been years since I performed. 🙈

Many thanks to @patty.zak for your endless hours of instruction, filled with lots of laughs at me trying to get it right! (And for correcting my turned out ballet feet! 🦆) 
Dance always came easy to me, but salsa is a completely different ball game...

Swipe to see photos from my dancing days as a young whippersnapper! 😄
Also a shout out to @taveras5505 for always being down to practice with me!

The top goal for my clients is to have their own natural nails with an overlay. Much of our feed is filled with perfectly pre-shaped gel extensions, so reshaping a natural nail to achieve a perfect looking shape, with all of its growing imperfections, can be a challenge. 
I've always preferred acrylic to accomplish perfecting the flaws in  natural nail growth. 

This is presently one of my longest natural nail clients with an acrylic overlay... and we cut them down this visit. @alexabriannemorales

An added bonus to a natural nail support underneath is that you will rarely have breakage. Start your clients out with a shorter length and allow their nails the time to grow out to their desired length. Not only does this decrease broken nails, it also allows your client time to adjust to working with a longer length nail so they'll be comfortable with the length once they reach their goal!
